#8901
The Introduction System~
   The WHO list and Introduction When you type the command "who", you will only
be able to see those people who have introduced themselves to you, OR any
member of the AoD staff that is online and visible.    

The Intro Command:
  This command is used to reveal your name to another character.  Once you have
another character's intro, you will be able to tell to them and their name
will appear instead of a description.  A character will only be able to know
a limited number of characters before they begin to forget people.

Usage: intro <victim>

The Greet Command:
  When a player is greeted, he or she will not forget the character who
has greeted them as fast as someone who does not greet them.

Usage: greet <victim>

  If you have not received any one's introduction, when you type in the
"who" command, you will only see yourself and any Imms who might be
present. However, at the bottom of the output, you will see something
that says "Characters playing:".  This will show you the number of other,
unintroduced players that are in the game with you.

There is also a newbie channel available, that is a global channel.  This
will allow you to ask experienced players questions and get advice.
Usage:  newbie (message)

Please continue north.
