#8902
The Rent System~
   To save your character and belongings, you need to rent instead of quitting
out of the game.  Rent is currently based on level, not on value of items and
so is not expensive.    
  There is also a long-term rent available, for those going on vacation or
whatever would keep a person from playing.  The command is: ltrent
It charges a one-time fee, and so is more costly than renting day to day, but
once you pay it, you may remain in rent as long as you wish.

  If you make an offer at an innkeeper, the innkeeper will tell you how 
many days of rent you have.  When those days run out, the innkeeper will be
forced to begin selling your things to pay for your room.  Thus, if you know
you are going to be away for several days or weeks, use the LTRENT function.

Please continue to the north.
~
