#8906
The Death and Fate System~
   Death is an unfortunate part of the game.  When your character is killed,
they will lose a great deal of experience, increasing as your character's level
increases.    

  There is also an aspect of the game called "fates".  Fates are more or less
the number of lives your character gets.  You start off with a large number of
these fates, and have a chance of getting additional ones with each level you
attain.  Every time you are killed, you lose one of these fates.  Death from
another player and death from a monster are counted against different limits.
Also, new characters (levels 1-5) do not lose fates when they die.  Once you
run out of either type of fates (i.e. none remaining), you character is dead
permanently.

    Using the attribute command will inform you when you are running low on
either type of your fates.  Also note: deaths of any kind no longer result
in the loss of any ability stats.

Please continue north.
~
