#8915
Spell Memorization~
   Let's say your character happens to be a level 1 Wizard.  You decide that
you are going to go try your skills against a monster and opt to use the Magic
Missile spell.  Assuming you have already practiced this skill at one of the
many guilds, you would type the following in order to begin memorizing the
spell: >mem 'magic missile' Age of Dragons will respond with an Okay message
and you will begin memorizing this spell.  In order to see which spells you
have completed memorizing, which spells you are currently memorizing, and which
spells you have left to memorize, type mem on a line by itself.  Continuing
with the above example, if you wanted to confirm that you were indeed
memorizing a Magic Missile spell, issue the following command: MEM

  This will show you:
[Spells Memorized]
None.
[Spells Being Memorized]
1: (5h)Magic Missile
[Spells Remaining] 1: 1/2 2: 1/1


  This tells us that we have no spells currently memorized, however we are
indeed currently memorizing a Magic Missile spell and it will be completed
in 5 game hours.

  This information also shows us we have one level 1 spell and one level
2 spell that can still be memorized.  When you have completed memorizing a
spell, the game will inform you with an appropriate message.  Once a spell
is memorized, it may be cast where appropriate.  After a spell has been cast,
the character will automatically begin memorizing the spell again so it may be
cast another time.

  If you wish to remove a spell either from memory or one being memorized,
the forget command must be used.

     If we decide we no longer wish to memorize the Magic Missile
spell, we could issue the following command to get rid of it: >forg 'Magic
Missile'.

