#8916
The Scribing System~
   Wizards and bards are required to scribe their spells into a spellbook
before they can cast them.    

SCRIBE
              [------- source -------]    [-- target --]
Usage: scribe <spellbook> 'spell name'    <spellbook>
       scribe <SCROLL>                    <spellbook>
       scribe 'spell name'                <blank_scroll>
This skill allows a Wizard to copy new spells into his/her spellbook,
copy spells from one spellbook to another, and copy spells from memory
to blank parchment for later use as a scroll.  A very powerful skill indeed,
that has a certain degree of danger when performed improperly.

